35// A structure representing a containing LetStmt, IfThenElse, or For
36// loop. Used in build_provide_loop_nest below. Both If and IfInner represent
37// IfThenElse stmts, however, IfInner should not be reordered to outside of
38// a for loop.
39struct Container {
40 enum Type { For,
41 Let,
42 If,
43 IfInner };
44 Type type;
45 // If it's a for loop, the index in the dims list.
46 int dim_idx;
47 string name;
48 Expr value;
49
50 Container(Type type, int dim_idx, string name, Expr value)
51 : type(type), dim_idx(dim_idx), name(std::move(name)), value(std::move(value)) {
52 }
53};
54
55bool var_name_match(const string &v1, const string &v2) {
56 return ((v1 == v2) ||
57 Internal::ends_with(v1, "." + v2) ||
58 Internal::ends_with(v2, "." + v1));
59}

61class ContainsImpureCall : public IRVisitor {
62 using IRVisitor::visit;
63
64 void visit(const Call *op) override {
65 if (!op->is_pure()) {
66 result = true;
67 } else {
68 IRVisitor::visit(op);
69 }
70 }
71
72public:
73 bool result = false;
74};
75
76bool contains_impure_call(const Expr &expr) {
77 ContainsImpureCall is_not_pure;
78 expr.accept(&is_not_pure);
79 return is_not_pure.result;
80}

82// Build a loop nest about a provide node using a schedule
83Stmt build_loop_nest(
84 const Stmt &body,
85 const string &prefix,
86 int start_fuse,
87 const Function &func,
88 const Definition &def,
89 bool is_update) {
90 const auto &dims = func.args();
91 const auto &func_s = func.schedule();
92 const auto &stage_s = def.schedule();
93 const auto &predicates = def.split_predicate();
94
95 // We'll build it from inside out, starting from the body,
96 // then wrapping it in for loops.
97 Stmt stmt = body;
98
99 // A map of the dimensions for which we know the extent is a
100 // multiple of some Expr. This can happen due to a bound, or
101 // align_bounds directive, or if a dim comes from the inside
102 // of a split.
103 map<string, Expr> dim_extent_alignment;
104
105 // First hunt through the bounds for them.
106 for (const Bound &i : func_s.bounds()) {
107 if (i.extent.defined()) {
108 dim_extent_alignment[i.var] = i.extent;
109 }
110 if (i.modulus.defined()) {
111 dim_extent_alignment[i.var] = i.modulus;
112 }
113 }
114 // Then use any reduction domain.
115 for (const ReductionVariable &i : stage_s.rvars()) {
116 dim_extent_alignment[i.var] = i.extent;
117 }
118
119 vector<Split> splits = stage_s.splits();
120
121 // Define the function args in terms of the loop variables using the splits
122 for (const Split &split : splits) {
123 vector<ApplySplitResult> splits_result = apply_split(split, is_update, prefix, dim_extent_alignment);
124
125 for (const auto &res : splits_result) {
126 if (res.is_substitution()) {
127 stmt = substitute(res.name, res.value, stmt);
128 } else if (res.is_let()) {
129 stmt = LetStmt::make(res.name, res.value, stmt);
130 } else {
131 internal_assert(res.is_predicate());
132 stmt = IfThenElse::make(res.value, stmt, Stmt());
133 }
134 }
135 }
136
137 // Order the Ifs, Fors, and Lets for bounds inference
138 // to generate tighter bounds and put the bound variables
139 // in the right place.
140 // This is not a generic loop invariant code motion step.
141 // In particular there are dangling references to bound
142 // variables that are not defined yet, so we can't rely
143 // the loop invariant code motion pass.
144
145 // All containing lets and fors. Outermost first.
146 vector<Container> nest;
147 nest.reserve(stage_s.dims().size());
148
149 // Put the desired loop nest into the containers vector.
150 for (int i = (int)stage_s.dims().size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
151 const Dim &dim = stage_s.dims()[i];
152 nest.emplace_back(Container::For, i, prefix + dim.var, Expr());
153 }
154
155 vector<Container> pred_container;
156 // Strip off the lets/ifs into the containers vector.
157 while (!stmt.same_as(body)) {
158 const auto *let = stmt.as<LetStmt>();
159 const auto *if_else = stmt.as<IfThenElse>();
160 if (let) {
161 nest.emplace_back(Container::Let, 0, let->name, let->value);
162 stmt = let->body;
163 } else if (if_else && !if_else->else_case.defined()) {
164 pred_container.emplace_back(Container::If, 0, "", if_else->condition);
165 stmt = if_else->then_case;
166 } else {
167 break;
168 }
169 }
170
171 // Add appropriate predicates on the fused loop vars to ensure we don't
172 // go out of bounds. Ignore the __outermost dims since it's going to be
173 // removed later anyway. These have to be added as outermost as possible as
174 // some let stmts (e.g. the rebase let stmt) might depend on this vars;
175 // otherwise, this may mess up the bounds_touched computation.
176 int n_predicates_inner = 0;
177 for (int i = start_fuse; (i >= 0) && (i < (int)stage_s.dims().size() - 1); ++i) {
178 string dim_var = prefix + stage_s.dims()[i].var;
179 Expr var = Variable::make(Int(32), dim_var);
180 Expr max = Variable::make(Int(32), dim_var + ".loop_max");
181 Expr min = Variable::make(Int(32), dim_var + ".loop_min");
182 // Use 'var', the variable which bounds we're constraining as the
183 // container name, so that we can use it later to check if a LetStmt
184 // value depends on 'var'.
185 nest.emplace_back(Container::IfInner, 0, dim_var, likely(var >= min));
186 nest.emplace_back(Container::IfInner, 0, dim_var, likely(var <= max));
187 n_predicates_inner += 2;
188 }
189
190 // Put all the reduction domain predicates into the containers vector.
191 for (Expr pred : predicates) {
192 pred = qualify(prefix, pred);
193 // Add a likely qualifier if there isn't already one
194 if (Call::as_intrinsic(pred, {Call::likely, Call::likely_if_innermost})) {
195 pred = likely(pred);
196 }
197 pred_container.emplace_back(Container::If, 0, "", pred);
198 }
199 int n_predicates = (int)(pred_container.size());
200
201 nest.insert(nest.end(), pred_container.begin(), pred_container.end());
202
203 // Resort the containers vector so that lets are as far outwards
204 // as possible. Use reverse insertion sort. Start at the first letstmt.
205 for (int i = (int)stage_s.dims().size(); i < (int)nest.size() - n_predicates_inner - n_predicates; i++) {
206 // Only push up LetStmts.
207 internal_assert(nest[i].value.defined());
208 internal_assert(nest[i].type == Container::Let);
209
210 for (int j = i - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
211 // Try to push it up by one.
212 internal_assert(nest[j + 1].value.defined());
213 if (!expr_uses_var(nest[j + 1].value, nest[j].name)) {
214 std::swap(nest[j + 1], nest[j]);
215 } else {
216 break;
217 }
218 }
219 }
220
221 // Sort the predicate guards for the fused loops so they are as far outwards
222 // as possible. IfInnner should not be reordered to outside of a for loop.
223 for (int i = (int)nest.size() - n_predicates_inner - n_predicates;
224 i < (int)nest.size() - n_predicates;
225 i++) {
226 // Only push up IfThenElse.
227 internal_assert(nest[i].value.defined());
228 internal_assert(nest[i].type == Container::IfInner);
229
230 // Cannot lift out the predicate guard if it contains call to non-pure function
231 if (contains_impure_call(nest[i].value)) {
232 continue;
233 }
234
235 for (int j = i - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
236 // Try to push it up by one.
237 internal_assert(nest[j + 1].value.defined());
238
239 if (!expr_uses_var(nest[j + 1].value, nest[j].name) &&
240 (nest[j].type != Container::For)) {
241 std::swap(nest[j + 1], nest[j]);
242 } else {
243 break;
244 }
245 }
246 }
247
248 // Sort the ifs so they are as far outwards as possible.
249 // BoxesTouched trims the domain of a variable within a scope of if-then-else
250 // based on the likely condition. However, it doesn't do it transitively; it
251 // doesn't trim the domains of other variables that directly/indirectly
252 // depend on the original variable in the likely condition outside the scope
253 // of the if-then-else. That's why it's necessary to move the ifs as far
254 // outwards as possible, so that those variables can have tighter bounds.
255 for (int i = (int)nest.size() - n_predicates; i < (int)nest.size(); i++) {
256 // Only push up IfThenElse.
257 internal_assert(nest[i].value.defined());
258 internal_assert(nest[i].type == Container::If);
259
260 // Cannot lift out the 'if' if it contains call to non-pure function
261 if (contains_impure_call(nest[i].value)) {
262 continue;
263 }
264
265 for (int j = i - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
266 // Try to push it up by one.
267 internal_assert(nest[j + 1].value.defined());
268
269 if (!expr_uses_var(nest[j + 1].value, nest[j].name)) {
270 std::swap(nest[j + 1], nest[j]);
271 } else {
272 break;
273 }
274 }
275 }
276
277 // Rewrap the statement in the containing lets and fors.
278 for (int i = (int)nest.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
279 if (nest[i].type == Container::Let) {
280 internal_assert(nest[i].value.defined());
281 stmt = LetStmt::make(nest[i].name, nest[i].value, stmt);
282 } else if ((nest[i].type == Container::If) || (nest[i].type == Container::IfInner)) {
283 internal_assert(nest[i].value.defined());
284 stmt = IfThenElse::make(nest[i].value, stmt, Stmt());
285 } else {
286 internal_assert(nest[i].type == Container::For);
287 const Dim &dim = stage_s.dims()[nest[i].dim_idx];
288 Expr min = Variable::make(Int(32), nest[i].name + ".loop_min");
289 Expr extent = Variable::make(Int(32), nest[i].name + ".loop_extent");
290 stmt = For::make(nest[i].name, min, extent, dim.for_type, dim.device_api, stmt);
291 }
292 }
293
294 // Define the bounds on the split dimensions using the bounds
295 // on the function args. If it is a purify, we should use the bounds
296 // from the dims instead.
297 for (size_t i = splits.size(); i > 0; i--) {
298 const Split &split = splits[i - 1];
299
300 vector<std::pair<string, Expr>> let_stmts = compute_loop_bounds_after_split(split, prefix);
301 for (const auto &let_stmt : let_stmts) {
302 stmt = LetStmt::make(let_stmt.first, let_stmt.second, stmt);
303 }
304 }
305
306 // Define the bounds on the outermost dummy dimension.
307 {
308 string o = prefix + Var::outermost().name();
309 stmt = LetStmt::make(o + ".loop_min", 0, stmt);
310 stmt = LetStmt::make(o + ".loop_max", 0, stmt);
311 stmt = LetStmt::make(o + ".loop_extent", 1, stmt);
312 }
313
314 // Define the loop mins and extents in terms of the mins and maxs produced by bounds inference
315 for (const std::string &i : dims) {
316 string var = prefix + i;
317 Expr max = Variable::make(Int(32), var + ".max");
318 Expr min = Variable::make(Int(32), var + ".min"); // Inject instance name here? (compute instance names during lowering)
319 stmt = LetStmt::make(var + ".loop_extent",
320 (max + 1) - min,
321 stmt);
322 stmt = LetStmt::make(var + ".loop_min", min, stmt);
323 stmt = LetStmt::make(var + ".loop_max", max, stmt);
324 }
325
326 // Define the loop mins and extents for the reduction domain (if there is any)
327 // in terms of the mins and maxs produced by bounds inference
328 for (const ReductionVariable &rv : stage_s.rvars()) {
329 string p = prefix + rv.var;
330 Expr rmin = Variable::make(Int(32), p + ".min");
331 Expr rmax = Variable::make(Int(32), p + ".max");
332 stmt = LetStmt::make(p + ".loop_min", rmin, stmt);
333 stmt = LetStmt::make(p + ".loop_max", rmax, stmt);
334 stmt = LetStmt::make(p + ".loop_extent", rmax - rmin + 1, stmt);
335 }
336
337 return stmt;
338}

340// Build a loop nest about a provide node using a schedule
341Stmt build_provide_loop_nest(const map<string, Function> &env,
342 const string &prefix,
343 const Function &func,
344 const Definition &def,
345 int start_fuse,
346 bool is_update) {
347
348 internal_assert(!is_update == def.is_init());
349
350 // Default stored values
351 vector<Expr> site(def.args().size());
352 vector<Expr> values(def.values().size());
353 for (size_t i = 0; i < values.size(); i++) {
354 Expr v = def.values()[i];
355 v = qualify(prefix, v);
356 values[i] = v;
357 debug(3) << "Value " << i << " = " << v << "\n";
358 }
359
360 // Default stored locations
361 for (size_t i = 0; i < def.args().size(); i++) {
362 Expr s = def.args()[i];
363 s = qualify(prefix, s);
364 site[i] = s;
365 debug(3) << "Site " << i << " = " << s << "\n";
366 }
367
368 // Make the (multi-dimensional multi-valued) store node.
369 Stmt body = Provide::make(func.name(), values, site);
370 if (def.schedule().atomic()) { // Add atomic node.
371 bool any_unordered_parallel = false;
372 for (const auto &d : def.schedule().dims()) {
373 any_unordered_parallel |= is_unordered_parallel(d.for_type);
374 }
375 if (any_unordered_parallel) {
376 // If required, we will allocate a mutex buffer called func.name() + ".mutex"
377 // The buffer is added in the AddAtomicMutex pass.
378 body = Atomic::make(func.name(), func.name() + ".mutex", body);
379 } else {
380 // No mutex is required if there is no parallelism, and it
381 // wouldn't work if all parallelism is synchronous
382 // (e.g. vectorization). Vectorization and the like will
383 // need to handle atomic nodes specially, by either
384 // emitting VectorReduce ops or scalarizing.
385 body = Atomic::make(func.name(), std::string{}, body);
386 }
387 }
388
389 // Default schedule/values if there is no specialization
390 Stmt stmt = build_loop_nest(body, prefix, start_fuse, func, def, is_update);
391 stmt = inject_placeholder_prefetch(stmt, env, prefix, def.schedule().prefetches());
392
393 // Make any specialized copies
394 const vector<Specialization> &specializations = def.specializations();
395 for (size_t i = specializations.size(); i > 0; i--) {
396 const Specialization &s = specializations[i - 1];
397 if (s.failure_message.empty()) {
398 Stmt then_case = build_provide_loop_nest(env, prefix, func, s.definition, start_fuse, is_update);
399 stmt = IfThenElse::make(s.condition, then_case, stmt);
400 } else {
401 internal_assert(equal(s.condition, const_true()));
402 // specialize_fail() should only be possible on the final specialization
403 internal_assert(i == specializations.size());
404 Expr specialize_fail_error =
405 Internal::Call::make(Int(32),
406 "halide_error_specialize_fail",
407 {StringImm::make(s.failure_message)},
408 Internal::Call::Extern);
409 // Since this is the final specialization, we can make
410 // this the else clause
411 stmt = AssertStmt::make(const_false(), specialize_fail_error);
412 }
413 }
414
415 return stmt;
416}

418// Turn a function into a loop nest that computes it. It will
419// refer to external vars of the form function_name.arg_name.min
420// and function_name.arg_name.extent to define the bounds over
421// which it should be realized. It will compute at least those
422// bounds (depending on splits, it may compute more). This loop
423// won't do any allocation.
424Stmt build_extern_produce(const map<string, Function> &env, Function f, const Target &target) {
425 // Call the external function
426
427 // Build an argument list
428 vector<Expr> extern_call_args;
429 const vector<ExternFuncArgument> &args = f.extern_arguments();
430
431 const string &extern_name = f.extern_function_name();
432
433 // We need to generate crops of the input and output buffers if the
434 // extern stage has some non-extern loops, aside from the outermost
435 // placeholder.
436 bool needs_crops = false;
437 if (!f.definition().schedule().dims().empty()) {
438 size_t extern_count = 0;
439 for (const Dim &d : f.definition().schedule().dims()) {
440 extern_count += d.for_type == ForType::Extern ? 1 : 0;
441 }
442 needs_crops = extern_count + 1 < f.definition().schedule().dims().size();
443 }
444
445 vector<pair<string, Expr>> lets;
446
447 // Iterate through all of the input args to the extern
448 // function building a suitable argument list for the
449 // extern function call.
450 vector<pair<Expr, int>> buffers_to_annotate;
451 vector<Expr> buffers_contents_to_annotate;
452 vector<pair<Expr, string>> buffers_to_check;
453 vector<pair<Expr, Expr>> cropped_buffers;
454 for (const ExternFuncArgument &arg : args) {
455 if (arg.is_expr()) {
456 extern_call_args.push_back(arg.expr);
457 } else if (arg.is_func()) {
458 Function input(arg.func);
459 if (!needs_crops && input.schedule().store_level() == input.schedule().compute_level()) {
460 for (int k = 0; k < input.outputs(); k++) {
461 string buf_name = input.name();
462 if (input.outputs() > 1) {
463 buf_name += "." + std::to_string(k);
464 }
465 buf_name += ".buffer";
466 Expr buffer = Variable::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), buf_name);
467 extern_call_args.push_back(buffer);
468 buffers_to_annotate.emplace_back(buffer, input.dimensions());
469 buffers_contents_to_annotate.push_back(buffer);
470 }
471 } else {
472 // Make a local crop of just the region required,
473 // in case the input was folded. We have no
474 // protocol for passing folded buffers to extern
475 // stages, so if the fold does indeed occur, we'll
476 // assert later that the crop doesn't cross over a
477 // fold.
478 string stage_name = input.name() + ".s" + std::to_string(input.updates().size()) + ".";
479 const vector<string> &input_args = input.args();
480 for (int k = 0; k < input.outputs(); k++) {
481 string src_buf_name = input.name();
482 if (input.outputs() > 1) {
483 src_buf_name += "." + std::to_string(k);
484 }
485 src_buf_name += ".buffer";
486 Expr src_buffer = Variable::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), src_buf_name);
487
488 Expr alloca_size = Call::make(Int(32), Call::size_of_halide_buffer_t, {}, Call::Intrinsic);
489 Expr cropped_input = Call::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), Call::alloca,
490 {alloca_size}, Call::Intrinsic);
491
492 vector<Expr> args(5);
493 args[0] = cropped_input;
494 args[1] = Call::make(type_of<struct halide_dimension_t *>(), Call::alloca,
495 {(int)sizeof(halide_dimension_t) * input.dimensions()}, Call::Intrinsic);
496 args[2] = src_buffer;
497
498 vector<Expr> mins, extents;
499 internal_assert(input.dimensions() == (int)input_args.size());
500 for (const string &arg : input_args) {
501 string var = stage_name + arg;
502 Expr min = Variable::make(Int(32), var + ".min");
503 Expr max = Variable::make(Int(32), var + ".max");
504 mins.push_back(min);
505 extents.push_back(max - min + 1);
506 }
507 args[3] = Call::make(type_of<const int *>(), Call::make_struct, mins, Call::Intrinsic);
508 args[4] = Call::make(type_of<const int *>(), Call::make_struct, extents, Call::Intrinsic);
509
510 cropped_input = Call::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), Call::buffer_crop,
511 args, Call::Extern);
512
513 string buf_name = input.name() + "." + std::to_string(k) + ".tmp_buffer";
514 extern_call_args.push_back(Variable::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), buf_name));
515 buffers_to_annotate.emplace_back(extern_call_args.back(), input.dimensions());
516 buffers_contents_to_annotate.push_back(cropped_input);
517 cropped_buffers.emplace_back(extern_call_args.back(), src_buffer);
518 lets.emplace_back(buf_name, cropped_input);
519 }
520 }
521 } else if (arg.is_buffer()) {
522 Buffer<> b = arg.buffer;
523 Parameter p(b.type(), true, b.dimensions(), b.name());
524 p.set_buffer(b);
525 Expr buf = Variable::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), b.name() + ".buffer", p);
526 extern_call_args.push_back(buf);
527 buffers_to_annotate.emplace_back(buf, b.dimensions());
528 buffers_contents_to_annotate.push_back(buf);
529 } else if (arg.is_image_param()) {
530 Parameter p = arg.image_param;
531 Expr buf = Variable::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), p.name() + ".buffer", p);
532 extern_call_args.push_back(buf);
533 // Do not annotate ImageParams: both the halide_buffer_t itself,
534 // and the contents it points to, should be filled by the caller;
535 // if we mark it here, we might mask a missed initialization.
536 // buffers_to_annotate.push_back(buf);
537 // buffers_contents_to_annotate.push_back(buf);
538 } else {
539 internal_error << "Bad ExternFuncArgument type\n";
540 }
541 }
542
543 // Grab the halide_buffer_t's representing the output. If the
544 // store level matches the compute level, then we can use the
545 // ones already injected by allocation bounds inference. If
546 // it's the output to the pipeline then it will similarly be
547 // in the symbol table.
548 if (!needs_crops && f.schedule().store_level() == f.schedule().compute_level()) {
549 for (int j = 0; j < f.outputs(); j++) {
550 string buf_name = f.name();
551 if (f.outputs() > 1) {
552 buf_name += "." + std::to_string(j);
553 }
554 buf_name += ".buffer";
555 Expr buffer = Variable::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), buf_name);
556 extern_call_args.push_back(buffer);
557 // Since this is a temporary, internal-only buffer, make sure it's marked.
558 // (but not the contents! callee is expected to fill that in.)
559 buffers_to_annotate.emplace_back(buffer, f.dimensions());
560 buffers_to_check.emplace_back(buffer, buf_name);
561 }
562 } else {
563 // Store level doesn't match compute level. Make an output
564 // buffer just for this subregion.
565 string stage_name = f.name() + ".s0.";
566 const vector<string> &f_args = f.args();
567 for (int j = 0; j < f.outputs(); j++) {
568 string src_buf_name = f.name();
569 if (f.outputs() > 1) {
570 src_buf_name += "." + std::to_string(j);
571 }
572 src_buf_name += ".buffer";
573 Expr src_buffer = Variable::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), src_buf_name);
574
575 Expr alloca_size = Call::make(Int(32), Call::size_of_halide_buffer_t, {}, Call::Intrinsic);
576 Expr output_buffer_t = Call::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), Call::alloca,
577 {alloca_size}, Call::Intrinsic);
578
579 vector<Expr> args(5);
580 args[0] = output_buffer_t;
581 args[1] = Call::make(type_of<struct halide_dimension_t *>(), Call::alloca,
582 {(int)sizeof(halide_dimension_t) * f.dimensions()}, Call::Intrinsic);
583 args[2] = src_buffer;
584
585 vector<Expr> mins, extents;
586 internal_assert(f.dimensions() == (int)f_args.size());
587 for (const string &arg : f_args) {
588 string var = stage_name + arg;
589 Expr min = Variable::make(Int(32), var + ".min");
590 Expr max = Variable::make(Int(32), var + ".max");
591 mins.push_back(min);
592 extents.push_back(max - min + 1);
593 }
594 args[3] = Call::make(type_of<const int *>(), Call::make_struct, mins, Call::Intrinsic);
595 args[4] = Call::make(type_of<const int *>(), Call::make_struct, extents, Call::Intrinsic);
596
597 output_buffer_t = Call::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), Call::buffer_crop, args,
598 Call::Extern);
599
600 string buf_name = f.name() + "." + std::to_string(j) + ".tmp_buffer";
601 extern_call_args.push_back(Variable::make(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>(), buf_name));
602 // Since this is a temporary, internal-only buffer, make sure it's marked.
603 // (but not the contents! callee is expected to fill that in.)
604 buffers_to_annotate.emplace_back(extern_call_args.back(), f.dimensions());
605 cropped_buffers.emplace_back(extern_call_args.back(), src_buffer);
606 lets.emplace_back(buf_name, output_buffer_t);
607 buffers_to_check.emplace_back(extern_call_args.back(), buf_name);
608 }
609 }
610
611 Stmt pre_call, post_call;
612 if (target.has_feature(Target::MSAN)) {
613 // Mark the buffers as initialized before calling out.
614 for (const auto &p : buffers_to_annotate) {
615 Expr buffer = p.first;
616 int dimensions = p.second;
617 // Return type is really 'void', but no way to represent that in our IR.
618 // Precedent (from halide_print, etc) is to use Int(32) and ignore the result.
619 Expr sizeof_buffer_t = cast<uint64_t>(
620 Call::make(Int(32), Call::size_of_halide_buffer_t, {}, Call::Intrinsic));
621 Stmt mark_buffer =
622 Evaluate::make(Call::make(Int(32), "halide_msan_annotate_memory_is_initialized",
623 {buffer, sizeof_buffer_t}, Call::Extern));
624 Expr shape = Call::make(type_of<halide_dimension_t *>(), Call::buffer_get_shape, {buffer},
625 Call::Extern);
626 Expr shape_size = Expr((uint64_t)(sizeof(halide_dimension_t) * dimensions));
627 Stmt mark_shape =
628 Evaluate::make(Call::make(Int(32), "halide_msan_annotate_memory_is_initialized",
629 {shape, shape_size}, Call::Extern));
630
631 mark_buffer = Block::make(mark_buffer, mark_shape);
632
633 if (!is_no_op(pre_call)) {
634 pre_call = Block::make(pre_call, mark_buffer);
635 } else {
636 pre_call = mark_buffer;
637 }
638 }
639 for (const auto &buffer : buffers_contents_to_annotate) {
640 // Return type is really 'void', but no way to represent that in our IR.
641 // Precedent (from halide_print, etc) is to use Int(32) and ignore the result.
642 Stmt mark_contents = Evaluate::make(
643 Call::make(Int(32), "halide_msan_annotate_buffer_is_initialized", {buffer}, Call::Extern));
644 if (!is_no_op(pre_call)) {
645 pre_call = Block::make(pre_call, mark_contents);
646 } else {
647 pre_call = mark_contents;
648 }
649 }
650 // Check the output buffer(s) from define_extern() calls to be sure they are fully initialized.
651 for (const auto &p : buffers_to_check) {
652 Expr buffer = p.first;
653 string buf_name = p.second;
654 Stmt check_contents = Evaluate::make(
655 Call::make(Int(32), "halide_msan_check_buffer_is_initialized", {buffer, Expr(buf_name)}, Call::Extern));
656 if (!is_no_op(post_call)) {
657 post_call = Block::make(post_call, check_contents);
658 } else {
659 post_call = check_contents;
660 }
661 }
662 }
663
664 // Make the extern call
665 Expr e = f.make_call_to_extern_definition(extern_call_args, target);
666
667 // Check if it succeeded
668 string result_name = unique_name('t');
669 Expr result = Variable::make(Int(32), result_name);
670 Expr error = Call::make(Int(32), "halide_error_extern_stage_failed",
671 {extern_name, result}, Call::Extern);
672 Stmt check = AssertStmt::make(EQ::make(result, 0), error);
673
674 if (!cropped_buffers.empty()) {
675 // We need to clean up the temporary crops we made for the
676 // outputs in case any of them have device allocations.
677 vector<Expr> cleanup_args;
678
679 // Make a struct with the buffers and their uncropped parents
680 for (const auto &p : cropped_buffers) {
681 // The cropped halide_buffer_t
682 cleanup_args.push_back(p.first);
683 // Its parent
684 cleanup_args.push_back(p.second);
685 }
686
687 if (cropped_buffers.size() > 1) {
688 // NULL-terminate it
689 cleanup_args.push_back(make_zero(type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>()));
690 }
691
692 Expr cleanup_struct = Call::make(Handle(),
693 Call::make_struct,
694 cleanup_args,
695 Call::Intrinsic);
696
697 // Insert cleanup before checking the result of the extern stage.
698 string destructor_name = unique_name('d');
699 const char *fn = (cropped_buffers.size() == 1 ? "_halide_buffer_retire_crop_after_extern_stage" : "_halide_buffer_retire_crops_after_extern_stage");
700 Expr cleanup = Call::make(Int(32), fn, {cleanup_struct}, Call::Extern);
701 check = Block::make(Evaluate::make(cleanup), check);
702 }
703
704 check = LetStmt::make(result_name, e, check);
705
706 if (pre_call.defined()) {
707 check = Block::make(pre_call, check);
708 }
709
710 for (const auto &let : lets) {
711 check = LetStmt::make(let.first, let.second, check);
712 }
713
714 if (post_call.defined()) {
715 check = Block::make(check, post_call);
716 }
717
718 Definition f_def_no_pred = f.definition().get_copy();
719 f_def_no_pred.predicate() = const_true();
720 return build_loop_nest(check, f.name() + ".s0.", -1, f, f_def_no_pred, false);
721}
722
723// A schedule may include explicit bounds on some dimension. This
724// injects assertions that check that those bounds are sufficiently
725// large to cover the inferred bounds required.
726Stmt inject_explicit_bounds(Stmt body, Function func) {
727 const FuncSchedule &s = func.schedule();
728 for (size_t stage = 0; stage <= func.updates().size(); stage++) {
729 for (auto b : s.bounds()) {
730 string prefix = func.name() + ".s" + std::to_string(stage) + "." + b.var;
731 string min_name = prefix + ".min_unbounded";
732 string max_name = prefix + ".max_unbounded";
733 Expr min_var = Variable::make(Int(32), min_name);
734 Expr max_var = Variable::make(Int(32), max_name);
735 if (!b.min.defined()) {
736 b.min = min_var;
737 }
738 if (!b.extent.defined()) {
739 // This is just a bounds alignment, which always expands the region computed.
740 continue;
741 }
742
743 Expr max_val = (b.extent + b.min) - 1;
744 Expr min_val = b.min;
745
746 Expr check = (min_val <= min_var) && (max_val >= max_var);
747 Expr error_msg = Call::make(Int(32), "halide_error_explicit_bounds_too_small",
748 {b.var, func.name(), min_val, max_val, min_var, max_var},
749 Call::Extern);
750 body = Block::make(AssertStmt::make(check, error_msg), body);
751 }
752 }
753
754 return body;
755}

817class InjectStmt : public IRMutator {
818public:
819 const Stmt &injected_stmt;
820 bool found_level;
821 const LoopLevel &level;
822
823 InjectStmt(const Stmt &s, const LoopLevel &level)
824 : injected_stmt(s), found_level(false), level(level) {
825 }
826
827private:
828 using IRMutator::visit;
829
830 Stmt visit(const For *for_loop) override {
831 Stmt body = mutate(for_loop->body);
832
833 if (level.match(for_loop->name)) {
834 body = Block::make(body, injected_stmt);
835 found_level = true;
836 }
837
838 if (body.same_as(for_loop->body)) {
839 return for_loop;
840 } else {
841 return For::make(for_loop->name,
842 for_loop->min,
843 for_loop->extent,
844 for_loop->for_type,
845 for_loop->device_api,
846 body);
847 }
848 }
849};
850
851// Inject 'injected' into 'root' at 'level'.
852Stmt inject_stmt(Stmt root, Stmt injected, const LoopLevel &level) {
853 if (!root.defined()) {
854 return injected;
855 }
856 if (!injected.defined()) {
857 return root;
858 }
859 if (level.is_inlined() || level.is_root()) {
860 return Block::make(root, injected);
861 }
862 InjectStmt injector(injected, level);
863 root = injector.mutate(root);
864 internal_assert(injector.found_level);
865 return root;
866}

868// Collect all let stmts that define the loop min, max, and extent.
869class CollectBounds : public IRVisitor {

893class SubstituteFusedBounds : public IRMutator {
894public:
895 const map<string, Expr> &replacements;
896 explicit SubstituteFusedBounds(const map<string, Expr> &r)
897 : replacements(r) {
898 }
899
900private:
901 using IRMutator::visit;
902
903 Stmt visit(const For *op) override {
904 const auto *min_var = op->min.as<Variable>();
905 const auto *extent_var = op->extent.as<Variable>();
906 if (min_var && extent_var) {
907 Expr min_val, extent_val;
908 {
909 const auto &it = replacements.find(min_var->name);
910 if (it != replacements.end()) {
911 min_val = it->second;
912 }
913 }
914 {
915 const auto &it = replacements.find(extent_var->name);
916 if (it != replacements.end()) {
917 extent_val = it->second;
918 }
919 }
920 if (!min_val.defined() || !extent_val.defined()) {
921 return IRMutator::visit(op);
922 }
923
924 Stmt body = mutate(op->body);
925
926 size_t last_dot = op->name.rfind('.');
927 internal_assert(last_dot != string::npos);
928 string new_var = op->name.substr(0, last_dot) + ".fused." + op->name.substr(last_dot + 1);
929
930 ForType for_type = op->for_type;
931 DeviceAPI device_api = op->device_api;
932 if (is_const_one(extent_val)) {
933 // This is the child loop of a fused group. The real loop of the
934 // fused group is the loop of the parent function of the fused
935 // group. This child loop is just a scheduling point, and should
936 // never be a device transition, so we rewrite it to be a simple
937 // serial loop of extent 1."
938 for_type = ForType::Serial;
939 device_api = DeviceAPI::None;
940 }
941
942 Stmt stmt = For::make(new_var, Variable::make(Int(32), new_var + ".loop_min"),
943 Variable::make(Int(32), new_var + ".loop_extent"),
944 for_type, device_api, body);
945
946 // Add let stmts defining the bound of the renamed for-loop.
947 stmt = LetStmt::make(new_var + ".loop_min", min_val, stmt);
948 stmt = LetStmt::make(new_var + ".loop_max", simplify(min_val + extent_val - 1), stmt);
949 stmt = LetStmt::make(new_var + ".loop_extent", extent_val, stmt);
950 // Replace any reference to the old loop name with the new one.
951 stmt = substitute(op->name, Variable::make(Int(32), new_var), stmt);
952 return stmt;
953 } else {
954 return IRMutator::visit(op);
955 }
956 }
957};
958
959// The bounds of every loop exist in 'replacements' should be replaced. The
960// loop is also renamed by adding '.fused' in the original name before the
961// variable name.
962Stmt substitute_fused_bounds(Stmt s, const map<string, Expr> &replacements) {
963 if (!s.defined() || replacements.empty()) {
964 return s;
965 } else {
966 return SubstituteFusedBounds(replacements).mutate(s);
967 }
968}

970// Shift the iteration domain of a loop nest by some factor.
971class ShiftLoopNest : public IRMutator {
972 const map<string, Expr> &shifts; // Add the shift factor to the old var
973
974 using IRMutator::visit;
975
976 Stmt visit(const For *op) override {
977 Stmt stmt = IRMutator::visit(op);
978 const auto &iter = shifts.find(op->name);
979 if (iter != shifts.end()) {
980 debug(5) << "...Shifting for loop \"" << op->name << "\" by " << iter->second << "\n";
981 op = stmt.as<For>();
982 internal_assert(op);
983 Expr adjusted = Variable::make(Int(32), op->name) + iter->second;
984 Stmt body = substitute(op->name, adjusted, op->body);
985 stmt = For::make(op->name, op->min, op->extent, op->for_type, op->device_api, body);
986 }
987 return stmt;
988 }
989
990public:
991 explicit ShiftLoopNest(const map<string, Expr> &s)
992 : shifts(s) {
993 }
994
995 template<typename T>
996 static T apply_shift(const map<string, Expr> &shifts, const T &node) {
997 if (shifts.empty()) {
998 return node;
999 }
1000 ShiftLoopNest visitor(shifts);
1001 return visitor.mutate(node);
1002 }
1003};

1006 const string &name;
1007 const vector<Type> &types;
1008 const PrefetchDirective &prefetch;
1009
1010 PlaceholderPrefetch(const string &name, const vector<Type> &types, const PrefetchDirective &prefetch)
1011 : name(name),
1012 types(types),
1013 prefetch(prefetch) {

1017class InjectFunctionRealization : public IRMutator {
1018public:
1019 InjectFunctionRealization(const vector<Function> &funcs,
1020 const vector<bool> &is_output_list,
1021 const Target &target,
1022 const map<string, Function> &env)
1023 : funcs(funcs),
1024 is_output_list(is_output_list),
1025 target(target),
1026 env(env),
1027 compute_level(funcs[0].schedule().compute_level()) {
1028 }
1029
1030 bool found_compute_level() const {
1031 return _found_compute_level;
1032 }
1033 bool found_store_level() const {
1034 return _found_store_levels_for_funcs.size() == funcs.size();
1035 }
1036
1037protected:
1038 bool _found_compute_level{};
1039 std::set<string> _found_store_levels_for_funcs;
1040
1041 using IRMutator::visit;
1042
1043 Stmt visit(const For *for_loop) override {
1044 debug(3) << "Injecting " << funcs << " entering for-loop over " << for_loop->name << "\n";
1045 Stmt body = for_loop->body;
1046
1047 // Dig through any placeholder prefetches
1048 vector<PlaceholderPrefetch> placeholder_prefetches;
1049 while (const auto *p = body.as<Prefetch>()) {
1050 placeholder_prefetches.emplace_back(p->name, p->types, p->prefetch);
1051 body = p->body;
1052 }
1053
1054 // Dig through any let/if statements
1055 vector<pair<string, Expr>> containers;
1056 while (true) {
1057 if (const LetStmt *l = body.as<LetStmt>()) {
1058 const Call *promise_clamped = Call::as_intrinsic(l->value, {Call::promise_clamped});
1059 if (!promise_clamped && !is_pure(l->value)) {
1060 // The consumer of the Func we're injecting may be an
1061 // extern stage, which shows up in the IR as a let
1062 // stmt with a side-effecty RHS. We need to take care
1063 // not to blow past it and risk injecting the producer
1064 // *after* the consumer. In general it seems unwise to
1065 // reorder the computation of a Func past something
1066 // side-effecty, so we stop here.
1067 //
1068 // An exception is that it's good to walk inside a
1069 // promise_clamped intrinsic due to a GuardWithIf
1070 // split. It's safe and produces cleaner IR.
1071 break;
1072 }
1073 containers.emplace_back(l->name, l->value);
1074 body = l->body;
1075 } else if (const IfThenElse *i = body.as<IfThenElse>()) {
1076 if (!is_pure(i->condition) || i->else_case.defined()) {
1077 break;
1078 }
1079 containers.emplace_back(std::string{}, i->condition);
1080 body = i->then_case;
1081 } else {
1082 break;
1083 }
1084 }
1085
1086 // Fused pairs (compute_with) cannot have extern definitions. Thus this condition is only true when funcs
1087 // contains a single function to be lowered. Can't schedule extern things inside a vector for loop.
1088 if (funcs[0].has_extern_definition() &&
1089 funcs[0].schedule().compute_level().is_inlined() &&
1090 for_loop->for_type == ForType::Vectorized &&
1091 !function_is_already_realized_in_stmt(funcs[0], for_loop) &&
1092 function_is_used_in_stmt(funcs[0], for_loop)) {
1093
1094 // If we're trying to inline an extern function, schedule it here and bail out
1095 debug(2) << "Injecting realization of " << funcs[0].name() << " around node " << Stmt(for_loop) << "\n";
1096
1097 Stmt stmt = build_realize(build_pipeline_group(for_loop), funcs[0], is_output_list[0]);
1098 _found_compute_level = true;
1099 _found_store_levels_for_funcs.insert(funcs[0].name());
1100 return stmt;
1101 }
1102
1103 body = mutate(body);
1104
1105 if (compute_level.match(for_loop->name)) {
1106 debug(3) << "Found compute level at " << for_loop->name << "\n";
1107 body = build_pipeline_group(body);
1108 _found_compute_level = true;
1109 }
1110
1111 if (_found_compute_level) {
1112 for (size_t i = 0; i < funcs.size(); i++) {
1113 if (funcs[i].schedule().store_level().match(for_loop->name)) {
1114 debug(3) << "Found store level for " << funcs[i].name() << " at " << for_loop->name << "\n";
1115 body = build_realize_function_from_group(body, i);
1116 _found_store_levels_for_funcs.insert(funcs[i].name());
1117 }
1118 }
1119 }
1120
1121 // Reinstate the let/if statements
1122 for (size_t i = containers.size(); i > 0; i--) {
1123 auto p = containers[i - 1];
1124 if (p.first.empty()) {
1125 body = IfThenElse::make(p.second, body);
1126 } else {
1127 body = LetStmt::make(p.first, p.second, body);
1128 }
1129 }
1130
1131 // Reinstate the placeholder prefetches
1132 for (size_t i = placeholder_prefetches.size(); i > 0; i--) {
1133 body = Prefetch::make(placeholder_prefetches[i - 1].name,
1134 placeholder_prefetches[i - 1].types,
1135 Region(),
1136 placeholder_prefetches[i - 1].prefetch,
1137 const_true(),
1138 body);
1139 }
1140
1141 // Skips pointless allocation
1142 if (body.same_as(for_loop->body)) {
1143 return for_loop;
1144 } else {
1145 return For::make(for_loop->name,
1146 for_loop->min,
1147 for_loop->extent,
1148 for_loop->for_type,
1149 for_loop->device_api,
1150 body);
1151 }
1152 }
1153
1154 // If we're an inline update or extern, we may need to inject a realization around
1155 // the Provide node (or a Provide node surrounded by an Atomic).
1156 Stmt inline_to_provide(const std::string &provide_name, Stmt provide_op) {
1157 // none of the functions in a fused group can be inlined, so this will only
1158 // happen when we're lowering a single func.
1159 if (provide_name != funcs[0].name() &&
1160 !funcs[0].is_pure() &&
1161 funcs[0].schedule().compute_level().is_inlined() &&
1162 function_is_used_in_stmt(funcs[0], provide_op)) {
1163
1164 // Prefix all calls to func in op
1165 Stmt stmt = build_realize(build_pipeline_group(provide_op), funcs[0], is_output_list[0]);
1166 _found_compute_level = true;
1167 _found_store_levels_for_funcs.insert(funcs[0].name());
1168 return stmt;
1169 }
1170
1171 return provide_op;
1172 }
1173
1174 Stmt visit(const Provide *op) override {
1175 return inline_to_provide(op->name, op);
1176 }
1177
1178 Stmt visit(const Atomic *op) override {
1179 return inline_to_provide(op->producer_name, op);
1180 }
1181
1182private:
1183 const vector<Function> &funcs;
1184 const vector<bool> &is_output_list;
1185 const Target &target;
1186 const map<string, Function> &env;
1187 const LoopLevel &compute_level;
1188
1189 Stmt build_realize(Stmt s, const Function &func, bool is_output) {
1190 if (func.has_extern_definition()) {
1191 // Add an annotation to let bounds inference know that
1192 // this will write to the entire bounds required.
1193 vector<Expr> args;
1194 args.emplace_back(Variable::make(Handle(), func.name()));
1195 for (int i = 0; i < func.dimensions(); i++) {
1196 string prefix = func.name() + ".s0." + func.args()[i];
1197 string min_name = prefix + ".min";
1198 string max_name = prefix + ".max";
1199
1200 args.emplace_back(Variable::make(Int(32), min_name));
1201 args.emplace_back(Variable::make(Int(32), max_name));
1202 }
1203 Expr decl = Call::make(Int(32), Call::declare_box_touched, args, Call::Intrinsic);
1204 s = Block::make(Evaluate::make(decl), s);
1205 }
1206
1207 if (!is_output) {
1208 Region bounds;
1209 const string &name = func.name();
1210 const vector<string> &func_args = func.args();
1211 for (int i = 0; i < func.dimensions(); i++) {
1212 const string &arg = func_args[i];
1213 Expr min = Variable::make(Int(32), name + "." + arg + ".min_realized");
1214 Expr extent = Variable::make(Int(32), name + "." + arg + ".extent_realized");
1215 bounds.emplace_back(min, extent);
1216 }
1217
1218 s = Realize::make(name, func.output_types(), func.schedule().memory_type(), bounds, const_true(), s);
1219 }
1220
1221 // This is also the point at which we inject explicit bounds
1222 // for this realization.
1223 if (target.has_feature(Target::NoAsserts)) {
1224 return s;
1225 } else {
1226 return inject_explicit_bounds(s, func);
1227 }
1228 }
1229
1230 Stmt build_realize_function_from_group(Stmt s, int func_index) {
1231 if (function_is_already_realized_in_stmt(funcs[func_index], s)) {
1232 return s;
1233 }
1234 if (function_is_used_in_stmt(funcs[func_index], s) || is_output_list[func_index]) {
1235 s = build_realize(s, funcs[func_index], is_output_list[func_index]);
1236 }
1237
1238 return s;
1239 }
1240
1241 // Compute the shift factor required to align iteration of
1242 // a function stage with its fused parent loop nest.
1243 void compute_shift_factor(const Function &f, const string &prefix, const Definition &def,
1244 map<string, Expr> &bounds, map<string, Expr> &shifts) {
1245 if (!def.defined()) {
1246 return;
1247 }
1248
1249 const vector<Dim> &dims = def.schedule().dims(); // From inner to outer
1250 const LoopLevel &fuse_level = def.schedule().fuse_level().level;
1251 const map<string, LoopAlignStrategy> &align_strategy = def.schedule().fuse_level().align;
1252
1253 if (fuse_level.is_inlined() || fuse_level.is_root()) {
1254 return;
1255 }
1256
1257 int start_fuse;
1258 {
1259 const auto &iter = std::find_if(dims.begin(), dims.end(),
1260 [&fuse_level](const Dim &d) {
1261 return var_name_match(d.var, fuse_level.var().name());
1262 });
1263 internal_assert(iter != dims.end());
1264 start_fuse = (int)(iter - dims.begin());
1265 }
1266
1267 int fused_vars_num = dims.size() - start_fuse - 1;
1268
1269 const auto &env_iter = env.find(fuse_level.func());
1270 internal_assert(env_iter != env.end());
1271 const auto &parent_func = env_iter->second;
1272
1273 const auto &parent_def = (fuse_level.stage_index() == 0) ? parent_func.definition() : parent_func.update(fuse_level.stage_index() - 1);
1274 const vector<Dim> &parent_dims = parent_def.schedule().dims();
1275
1276 for (int i = start_fuse; i < (int)dims.size() - 1; ++i) {
1277 const string &var = dims[i].var;
1278 Expr shift_val;
1279 auto iter = align_strategy.begin();
1280 for (; iter != align_strategy.end(); ++iter) {
1281 if (var_name_match(var, iter->first)) {
1282 break;
1283 }
1284 }
1285
1286 if ((iter == align_strategy.end()) ||
1287 (iter->second == LoopAlignStrategy::NoAlign) ||
1288 (iter->second == LoopAlignStrategy::Auto)) {
1289 continue;
1290 }
1291
1292 string parent_prefix = fuse_level.func() + ".s" + std::to_string(fuse_level.stage_index()) + ".";
1293 int parent_var_index = (i - start_fuse) + (int)parent_dims.size() - 1 - fused_vars_num;
1294 internal_assert(parent_var_index >= 0);
1295 string parent_var = parent_dims[parent_var_index].var;
1296
1297 auto it_min = bounds.find(prefix + var + ".loop_min");
1298 auto it_max = bounds.find(prefix + var + ".loop_max");
1299 internal_assert((it_min != bounds.end()) && (it_max != bounds.end()));
1300
1301 if (iter->second == LoopAlignStrategy::AlignStart) {
1302 auto parent_min = bounds.find(parent_prefix + parent_var + ".loop_min");
1303 internal_assert(parent_min != bounds.end());
1304 shift_val = parent_min->second - it_min->second;
1305 } else {
1306 auto parent_max = bounds.find(parent_prefix + parent_var + ".loop_max");
1307 internal_assert(parent_max != bounds.end());
1308 shift_val = parent_max->second - it_max->second;
1309 }
1310
1311 internal_assert(shift_val.defined());
1312 shifts.emplace(prefix + var, simplify(-shift_val));
1313 it_min->second = simplify(shift_val + it_min->second);
1314 it_max->second = simplify(shift_val + it_max->second);
1315 }
1316 }
1317
1318 Stmt build_produce_definition(const Function &f, const string &prefix, const Definition &def, bool is_update,
1319 map<string, Expr> &replacements, vector<pair<string, Expr>> &add_lets) {
1320 const vector<Dim> &dims = def.schedule().dims(); // From inner to outer
1321 const LoopLevel &fuse_level = def.schedule().fuse_level().level;
1322
1323 size_t start_fuse = dims.size();
1324 if (!fuse_level.is_inlined() && !fuse_level.is_root()) {
1325 const auto &iter = std::find_if(dims.begin(), dims.end(),
1326 [&fuse_level](const Dim &d) {
1327 return var_name_match(d.var, fuse_level.var().name());
1328 });
1329 internal_assert(iter != dims.end());
1330 start_fuse = (size_t)(iter - dims.begin());
1331 }
1332
1333 // The bounds of the child fused loops should be replaced to refer to the
1334 // parent fused loop. Here, we are only collecting the ones we should
1335 // replace. The actual replacement is done later.
1336 for (const FusedPair &pair : def.schedule().fused_pairs()) {
1337 const auto &f2_it = env.find(pair.func_2);
1338 internal_assert(f2_it != env.end());
1339 const vector<Dim> &dims_2 =
1340 (pair.stage_2 == 0) ? f2_it->second.definition().schedule().dims() : f2_it->second.update((int)(pair.stage_2 - 1)).schedule().dims();
1341
1342 const auto &iter = std::find_if(dims.begin(), dims.end(),
1343 [&pair](const Dim &d) { return var_name_match(d.var, pair.var_name); });
1344 internal_assert(iter != dims.end());
1345 start_fuse = std::min(start_fuse, (size_t)(iter - dims.begin()));
1346 // Should ignore the __outermost dummy dimension.
1347 for (size_t i = (size_t)(iter - dims.begin()); i < dims.size() - 1; ++i) {
1348 string var_orig = pair.func_1 + ".s" + std::to_string(pair.stage_1) + "." + dims[i].var;
1349 Expr val = Variable::make(Int(32), var_orig);
1350
1351 int dim2_idx = (int)(dims_2.size() - (dims.size() - i));
1352 internal_assert(dim2_idx < (int)dims_2.size());
1353 string var = pair.func_2 + ".s" + std::to_string(pair.stage_2) + "." + dims_2[dim2_idx].var;
1354
1355 replacements.emplace(var + ".loop_extent", make_const(Int(32), 1));
1356 replacements.emplace(var + ".loop_min", val);
1357 replacements.emplace(var + ".loop_max", val);
1358 }
1359 }
1360
1361 Stmt produce = build_provide_loop_nest(env, prefix, f, def, (int)(start_fuse), is_update);
1362
1363 // Strip off the containing lets. The bounds of the parent fused loop
1364 // (i.e. the union bounds) might refer to them, so we need to move them
1365 // to the topmost position.
1366 while (const auto *let = produce.as<LetStmt>()) {
1367 add_lets.emplace_back(let->name, let->value);
1368 produce = let->body;
1369 }
1370 return produce;
1371 }
1372
1373 void collect_all_dependence_helper(const string &prefix, const Definition &def, const FusedPair &p,
1374 vector<FusedPair> &dependence, set<string> &visited) {
1375 visited.insert(prefix);
1376 dependence.push_back(p);
1377 for (const FusedPair &pair : def.schedule().fused_pairs()) {
1378 const auto &iter = env.find(pair.func_2);
1379 internal_assert(iter != env.end());
1380 const Function &f = iter->second;
1381 string prefix_2 = pair.func_2 + ".s" + std::to_string(pair.stage_2) + "." + pair.var_name;
1382 if (visited.find(prefix_2) == visited.end()) {
1383 const Definition &def_2 = (pair.stage_2 == 0) ? f.definition() : f.update((int)(pair.stage_2 - 1));
1384 collect_all_dependence_helper(prefix_2, def_2, pair, dependence, visited);
1385 }
1386 }
1387 }
1388
1389 // Collect all fused pairs that directly/indirectly related to 'def'
1390 vector<FusedPair> collect_all_dependence(const Definition &def) {
1391 set<string> visited;
1392 vector<FusedPair> dependence;
1393
1394 for (const FusedPair &pair : def.schedule().fused_pairs()) {
1395 const auto &iter = env.find(pair.func_2);
1396 internal_assert(iter != env.end());
1397 const Function &f = iter->second;
1398 string prefix = pair.func_2 + ".s" + std::to_string(pair.stage_2) + "." + pair.var_name;
1399 if (visited.find(prefix) == visited.end()) {
1400 const Definition &def_2 = (pair.stage_2 == 0) ? f.definition() : f.update((int)(pair.stage_2 - 1));
1401 collect_all_dependence_helper(prefix, def_2, pair, dependence, visited);
1402 }
1403 }
1404 return dependence;
1405 }
1406
1407 // Replace the bounds of the parent fused loop (i.e. the first one to be
1408 // realized in the group) with union of the bounds of the fused group.
1409 Stmt replace_parent_bound_with_union_bound(const Function &f, Stmt produce, const map<string, Expr> &bounds) {
1410 string prefix = f.name() + ".s0";
1411 const Definition &def = f.definition();
1412
1413 if (!def.defined()) {
1414 return produce;
1415 }
1416
1417 const vector<Dim> &dims = def.schedule().dims(); // From inner to outer
1418
1419 map<string, Expr> replacements;
1420
1421 vector<FusedPair> dependence = collect_all_dependence(def);
1422
1423 // Compute the union of the bounds of the fused loops.
1424 for (const FusedPair &pair : dependence) {
1425 const auto &f2_it = env.find(pair.func_2);
1426 internal_assert(f2_it != env.end());
1427 const vector<Dim> &dims_2 =
1428 (pair.stage_2 == 0) ? f2_it->second.definition().schedule().dims() :
1429 f2_it->second.update((int)(pair.stage_2 - 1)).schedule().dims();
1430
1431 const auto &iter = std::find_if(dims.begin(), dims.end(),
1432 [&pair](const Dim &d) { return var_name_match(d.var, pair.var_name); });
1433 internal_assert(iter != dims.end());
1434
1435 // Should ignore the __outermost dummy dimension.
1436 for (size_t i = (size_t)(iter - dims.begin()); i < dims.size() - 1; ++i) {
1437 // The child's dim might have slightly different name from
1438 // the parent, e.g. y.yi and yi.
1439 int dim2_idx = (int)(dims_2.size() - (dims.size() - i));
1440 internal_assert(dim2_idx < (int)dims_2.size());
1441
1442 string var_2 = pair.func_2 + ".s" + std::to_string(pair.stage_2) +
1443 "." + dims_2[dim2_idx].var;
1444 internal_assert(bounds.count(var_2 + ".loop_min"));
1445 internal_assert(bounds.count(var_2 + ".loop_max"));
1446 internal_assert(bounds.count(var_2 + ".loop_extent"));
1447 Expr min_2 = bounds.find(var_2 + ".loop_min")->second;
1448 Expr max_2 = bounds.find(var_2 + ".loop_max")->second;
1449 Expr extent_2 = bounds.find(var_2 + ".loop_extent")->second;
1450
1451 string var_1 = prefix + "." + dims[i].var;
1452 internal_assert(bounds.count(var_1 + ".loop_min"));
1453 internal_assert(bounds.count(var_1 + ".loop_max"));
1454 internal_assert(bounds.count(var_1 + ".loop_extent"));
1455
1456 Expr min_1, max_1;
1457 const auto &it = replacements.find(var_1 + ".loop_min");
1458 if (it == replacements.end()) {
1459 min_1 = bounds.find(var_1 + ".loop_min")->second;
1460 max_1 = bounds.find(var_1 + ".loop_max")->second;
1461 } else {
1462 min_1 = replacements.find(var_1 + ".loop_min")->second;
1463 max_1 = replacements.find(var_1 + ".loop_max")->second;
1464 }
1465
1466 // Extent is computed from min/max, so we don't find() it earlier.
1467 replacements[var_1 + ".loop_min"] = simplify(min(min_1, min_2));
1468 replacements[var_1 + ".loop_max"] = simplify(max(max_1, max_2));
1469 replacements[var_1 + ".loop_extent"] =
1470 simplify((replacements[var_1 + ".loop_max"] + 1) -
1471 replacements[var_1 + ".loop_min"]);
1472 }
1473 }
1474
1475 // Now, replace the bounds of the parent fused loops with the union bounds.
1476 produce = substitute_fused_bounds(produce, replacements);
1477 return produce;
1478 }
1479
1480 Stmt build_pipeline_group(Stmt consumer) {
1481 size_t num_skipped = 0;
1482 for (size_t i = 0; i < funcs.size(); ++i) {
1483 bool should_skip = function_is_already_realized_in_stmt(funcs[i], consumer) ||
1484 !(function_is_used_in_stmt(funcs[i], consumer) || is_output_list[i]);
1485 if (should_skip) {
1486 num_skipped += 1;
1487 }
1488 }
1489
1490 if (num_skipped == funcs.size()) {
1491 // All producers are skipped.
1492 return consumer;
1493 }
1494
1495 user_assert(num_skipped == 0) << "Fused groups must either be entirely used or unused\n";
1496
1497 // Order of the stages for building produce definitions.
1498 vector<pair<Function, int>> stage_order;
1499 // Inverse map from function name to the index.
1500 map<string, int> func_name_to_index;
1501 // Contains a number of dependencies which need to go first for a given stage of the function.
1502 vector<vector<int>> stage_dependencies(funcs.size());
1503
1504 // Holds the index of the function stage.
1505 struct FuncStageIndex {
1506 int func_index;
1507 int stage_index;
1508 };
1509
1510 // Adjacency list of dependencies. The structure is [func_index, stage_index, vector of the edges],
1511 // where edge is the index of the other function stage.
1512 vector<vector<vector<FuncStageIndex>>> adj_list(funcs.size());
1513
1514 // Initialize data structures.
1515 for (size_t i = 0; i < funcs.size(); i++) {
1516 stage_dependencies[i].resize(1 + funcs[i].updates().size(), 0);
1517 adj_list[i].resize(1 + funcs[i].updates().size());
1518 func_name_to_index[funcs[i].name()] = i;
1519 }
1520
1521 // Figure out dependencies between the stages.
1522 for (size_t i = 0; i < funcs.size(); i++) {
1523 auto prev_level = funcs[i].definition().schedule().fuse_level().level;
1524 {
1525 const auto &level = funcs[i].definition().schedule().fuse_level().level;
1526 if (!level.is_root() && !level.is_inlined()) {
1527 stage_dependencies[i][0]++;
1528 adj_list[func_name_to_index[level.func()]][level.stage_index()].push_back({(int)i, 0});
1529 }
1530 }
1531 for (size_t j = 0; j < funcs[i].updates().size(); ++j) {
1532 const auto &level = funcs[i].updates()[j].schedule().fuse_level().level;
1533 if (!level.is_root() && !level.is_inlined()) {
1534 stage_dependencies[i][j + 1]++;
1535 adj_list[func_name_to_index[level.func()]][level.stage_index()].push_back({(int)i, (int)j + 1});
1536
1537 // Let say that we have a stage f.update(p), which is scheduled to be computed_with
1538 // another stage g.update(q) (like f.update(p).compute_with(g.update(q), var)).
1539 // This means that the loop for f.update(p) will be injected into the loop for g.update(q).
1540 // Given that, for this to be correct, all stages of f up until (p - 1) must come
1541 // before g.update(q).
1542 // However, there is a special case here when two or more consecutive stages are computed
1543 // with the same stage. In this case, we won't be adding back edge to avoid creating cyclic
1544 // dependency.
1545 if (!(prev_level.func() == level.func() && prev_level.stage_index() == level.stage_index())) {
1546 for (size_t k = 0; k < j + 1; k++) {
1547 stage_dependencies[func_name_to_index[level.func()]][level.stage_index()]++;
1548 adj_list[i][k].push_back({func_name_to_index[level.func()], level.stage_index()});
1549 }
1550 }
1551 prev_level = level;
1552 }
1553 }
1554 }
1555
1556 size_t complete_count = 0;
1557 vector<size_t> stage_index(funcs.size());
1558 // This basically computes topological order, but exploits the fact that stages of the function
1559 // form linear order. Basically, we have a set of indices that point to the current stages
1560 // for each of the functions and should be considered as a next stage in the general order. They
1561 // are added to the order, only if all of their dependencies have been added already.
1562 while (complete_count < funcs.size()) {
1563 bool progress_made = false;
1564 for (size_t i = 0; i < funcs.size(); i++) {
1565 // We already added all stages of this function, so proceed to the next function.
1566 if (stage_index[i] == stage_dependencies[i].size()) {
1567 continue;
1568 }
1569 // Proceed as far as we can, so stages of the same function are bundled together.
1570 while (stage_index[i] < stage_dependencies[i].size()) {
1571 if (stage_dependencies[i][stage_index[i]] > 0) {
1572 break;
1573 }
1574 // Now that we are going to add a stage to the order, go over dependent nodes
1575 // and decrease their dependency count.
1576 for (size_t k = 0; k < adj_list[i][stage_index[i]].size(); k++) {
1577 const auto &edge = adj_list[i][stage_index[i]][k];
1578 internal_assert(stage_dependencies[edge.func_index][edge.stage_index] > 0);
1579 stage_dependencies[edge.func_index][edge.stage_index]--;
1580 }
1581 stage_order.emplace_back(funcs[i], stage_index[i]);
1582 stage_index[i]++;
1583 progress_made = true;
1584 }
1585 if (stage_index[i] == stage_dependencies[i].size()) {
1586 complete_count++;
1587 }
1588 }
1589 // Make sure that we made some progress, otherwise there is a cyclic dependency.
1590 if (!progress_made) {
1591 std::stringstream ss;
1592 ss << "There is a cycle inside of the fused group: \n";
1593 for (size_t i = 0; i < funcs.size(); i++) {
1594 if (stage_index[i] == stage_dependencies[i].size()) {
1595 continue;
1596 }
1597 ss << funcs[i].name() << ".s" << stage_index[i] << "has " << stage_dependencies[i][stage_index[i]]
1598 << "unsatisfied dependencies; \n";
1599 }
1600 user_assert(progress_made) << ss.str();
1601 }
1602 }
1603
1604 // Build the loops.
1605 Stmt producer;
1606 map<string, Expr> replacements;
1607 vector<pair<string, Expr>> add_lets;
1608
1609 for (const auto &func_stage : stage_order) {
1610 const auto &f = func_stage.first;
1611
1612 if (f.has_extern_definition() && (func_stage.second == 0)) {
1613 const Stmt &produceDef = Internal::build_extern_produce(env, f, target);
1614 producer = inject_stmt(producer, produceDef, LoopLevel::inlined().lock());
1615 continue;
1616 }
1617
1618 string def_prefix = f.name() + ".s" + std::to_string(func_stage.second) + ".";
1619 const auto &def = (func_stage.second == 0) ? f.definition() : f.updates()[func_stage.second - 1];
1620
1621 const Stmt &produceDef = build_produce_definition(f, def_prefix, def, func_stage.second > 0,
1622 replacements, add_lets);
1623 producer = inject_stmt(producer, produceDef, def.schedule().fuse_level().level);
1624 }
1625
1626 internal_assert(producer.defined());
1627
1628 // Rewrap the loop in the containing lets.
1629 for (size_t i = add_lets.size(); i > 0; --i) {
1630 const auto &b = add_lets[i - 1];
1631 producer = LetStmt::make(b.first, b.second, producer);
1632 }
1633
1634 // The original bounds of the loop nests (without any loop-fusion)
1635 auto bounds = CollectBounds::collect_bounds(producer);
1636
1637 // Compute the shift factors based on the alignment strategies
1638 // starting from the the parent (root loop) to the children. The root
1639 // loop bounds should remain unchanged.
1640 map<string, Expr> shifts;
1641 for (auto i = funcs.size(); i-- > 0;) {
1642 const auto &func = funcs[i];
1643 compute_shift_factor(func, func.name() + ".s0.", func.definition(), bounds, shifts);
1644 for (size_t j = 0; j < func.updates().size(); ++j) {
1645 string prefix = func.name() + ".s" + std::to_string(j + 1) + ".";
1646 compute_shift_factor(func, prefix, func.updates()[j], bounds, shifts);
1647 }
1648 }
1649 // Shift the loops.
1650 producer = ShiftLoopNest::apply_shift(shifts, producer);
1651
1652 // Replace all the child fused loops with the appropriate bounds
1653 // (i.e. the min/max should refer to the parent loop vars and the
1654 // extent should be one).
1655 producer = substitute_fused_bounds(producer, replacements);
1656
1657 // Replace the bounds of parent fused loop with union of bounds of
1658 // the fused loops.
1659 producer = replace_parent_bound_with_union_bound(funcs.back(), producer, bounds);
1660
1661 // Add the producer nodes.
1662 for (const auto &i : funcs) {
1663 producer = ProducerConsumer::make_produce(i.name(), producer);
1664 }
1665
1666 // Add the consumer nodes.
1667 for (size_t i = 0; i < funcs.size(); i++) {
1668 if (!is_output_list[i]) {
1669 consumer = ProducerConsumer::make_consume(funcs[i].name(), consumer);
1670 }
1671 }
1672
1673 if (is_no_op(consumer)) {
1674 // For the very first output to be scheduled, the consumer
1675 // Stmt can be a no-op. No point in preserving it.
1676 return producer;
1677 } else {
1678 return Block::make(producer, consumer);
1679 }
1680 }
1681};
1682
1683class ComputeLegalSchedules : public IRVisitor {
1684public:
1685 struct Site {
1686 bool is_parallel;
1687 LoopLevel loop_level;
1688 };
1689 vector<Site> sites_allowed;
1690 bool found;
1691
1692 ComputeLegalSchedules(Function f, const map<string, Function> &env)
1693 : found(false), func(std::move(f)), env(env) {
1694 }
1695
1696private:
1697 using IRVisitor::visit;
1698
1699 vector<Site> sites;
1700 Function func;
1701
1702 const map<string, Function> &env;
1703
1704 void visit(const For *f) override {
1705 f->min.accept(this);
1706 f->extent.accept(this);
1707 size_t first_dot = f->name.find('.');
1708 size_t last_dot = f->name.rfind('.');
1709 internal_assert(first_dot != string::npos && last_dot != string::npos);
1710 string func = f->name.substr(0, first_dot);
1711 string var = f->name.substr(last_dot + 1);
1712 LoopLevel loop_level;
1713 if (func.empty()) {
1714 internal_assert(!var.empty());
1715 loop_level = LoopLevel::root();
1716 } else {
1717 auto it = env.find(func);
1718 internal_assert(it != env.end()) << "Unable to find Function " << func << " in env (Var = " << var << ")\n";
1719 loop_level = LoopLevel(it->second, Var(var));
1720 }
1721 // Since we are now in the lowering phase, we expect all LoopLevels to be locked;
1722 // thus any new ones we synthesize we must explicitly lock.
1723 loop_level.lock();
1724 Site s = {f->is_parallel(), loop_level};
1725 sites.push_back(s);
1726 f->body.accept(this);
1727 sites.pop_back();
1728 }
1729
1730 void register_use() {
1731 if (!found) {
1732 found = true;
1733 sites_allowed = sites;
1734 } else {
1735 vector<Site> common_sites;
1736
1737 // Take the common sites between sites and sites_allowed
1738 for (const Site &s1 : sites) {
1739 for (const Site &s2 : sites_allowed) {
1740 if (s1.loop_level.match(s2.loop_level)) {
1741 common_sites.push_back(s1);
1742 break;
1743 }
1744 }
1745 }
1746
1747 sites_allowed.swap(common_sites);
1748 }
1749 }
1750
1751 void visit(const Call *c) override {
1752 IRVisitor::visit(c);
1753
1754 if (c->name == func.name()) {
1755 register_use();
1756 }
1757 }
1758
1759 void visit(const Variable *v) override {
1760 if (v->type.is_handle() &&
1761 starts_with(v->name, func.name() + ".") &&
1762 ends_with(v->name, ".buffer")) {
1763 register_use();
1764 }
1765 }
1766};
1767
1768string schedule_to_source(const Function &f, const LoopLevel &store_at, const LoopLevel &compute_at) {
1769 std::ostringstream ss;
1770 ss << f.name();
1771 if (compute_at.is_inlined()) {
1772 ss << ".compute_inline()";
1773 } else {
1774 if (!store_at.match(compute_at)) {
1775 if (store_at.is_root()) {
1776 ss << ".store_root()";
1777 } else {
1778 string store_var_name = store_at.var().name();
1779 if (store_var_name == Var::outermost().name()) {
1780 store_var_name = "Var::outermost()";
1781 }
1782 ss << ".store_at(" << store_at.func() << ", " << store_var_name << ")";
1783 }
1784 }
1785 if (compute_at.is_root()) {
1786 ss << ".compute_root()";
1787 } else {
1788 string compute_var_name = compute_at.var().name();
1789 if (compute_var_name == Var::outermost().name()) {
1790 compute_var_name = "Var::outermost()";
1791 }
1792 ss << ".compute_at(" << compute_at.func() << ", " << compute_var_name << ")";
1793 }
1794 }
1795 ss << ";";
1796 return ss.str();
1797}

1814 IRVisitor::visit(op);

1824class PrintUsesOfFunc : public IRVisitor {
1825 using IRVisitor::visit;
1826
1827 int indent = 1;
1828 string func, caller;
1829 bool last_print_was_ellipsis = false;
1830 std::ostream &stream;
1831
1832 Indentation get_indent() const {
1833 return Indentation{indent};
1834 }
1835
1836 void visit(const For *op) override {
1837 if (ends_with(op->name, Var::outermost().name()) ||
1838 ends_with(op->name, LoopLevel::root().lock().to_string())) {
1839 IRVisitor::visit(op);
1840 } else {
1841
1842 int old_indent = indent;
1843
1844 StmtUsesFunc uses(func);
1845 op->body.accept(&uses);
1846 if (!uses.result) {
1847 if (!last_print_was_ellipsis) {
1848 stream << get_indent() << "...\n";
1849 last_print_was_ellipsis = true;
1850 }
1851 } else {
1852 stream << get_indent() << "for " << op->name << ":\n";
1853 last_print_was_ellipsis = false;
1854 indent++;
1855 }
1856
1857 IRVisitor::visit(op);
1858 indent = old_indent;
1859 }
1860 }
1861
1862 void visit(const ProducerConsumer *op) override {
1863 if (op->is_producer) {
1864 string old_caller = caller;
1865 caller = op->name;
1866 op->body.accept(this);
1867 caller = old_caller;
1868 } else {
1869 IRVisitor::visit(op);
1870 }
1871 }
1872
1873 void visit(const Call *op) override {
1874 if (op->name == func) {
1875 stream << get_indent() << caller << " uses " << func << "\n";
1876 last_print_was_ellipsis = false;
1877 } else {
1878 IRVisitor::visit(op);
1879 }
1880 }
1881
1882 void visit(const Variable *op) override {
1883 if (op->type.is_handle() &&
1884 starts_with(op->name, func + ".") &&
1885 ends_with(op->name, ".buffer")) {
1886 stream << get_indent() << caller << " uses " << func << "\n";
1887 last_print_was_ellipsis = false;
1888 } else {
1889 IRVisitor::visit(op);
1890 }
1891 }
1892
1893public:
1894 PrintUsesOfFunc(string f, std::ostream &s)
1895 : func(std::move(f)), stream(s) {
1896 }
1897};
