1899// Check a schedule is legal, throwing an error if it is not. Returns
1900// whether or not a realization of the Func should be injected. Unused
1901// intermediate Funcs that somehow made it into the Func DAG can be
1902// discarded.
1903bool validate_schedule(Function f, const Stmt &s, const Target &target, bool is_output, const map<string, Function> &env) {
1904
1905 // If f is extern, check that none of its inputs are scheduled inline.
1906 if (f.has_extern_definition()) {
1907 for (const ExternFuncArgument &arg : f.extern_arguments()) {
1908 if (arg.is_func()) {
1909 Function g(arg.func);
1910 if (!g.is_wrapper() &&
1911 g.schedule().compute_level().is_inlined()) {
1912 user_error
1913 << "Func " << g.name() << " cannot be scheduled to be computed inline, "
1914 << "because it is used in the externally-computed function " << f.name() << "\n";
1915 }
1916 }
1917 }
1918
1919 // Check that extern stages do not have any non-extern loops
1920 // inside any extern loops, and all loop types are supported
1921 // for extern stages.
1922 const vector<Dim> &dims = f.definition().schedule().dims();
1923 bool is_extern = !dims.empty() ? dims.front().for_type == ForType::Extern : false;
1924 for (const Dim &i : dims) {
1925 switch (i.for_type) {
1926 case ForType::Extern:
1927 if (!is_extern) {
1928 user_error
1929 << "Externally defined Func " << f.name()
1930 << " cannot have extern loop " << i.var
1931 << " outside a non-extern loop.\n";
1932 }
1933 break;
1934 case ForType::Serial:
1935 case ForType::Parallel:
1936 case ForType::Unrolled:
1937 is_extern = false;
1938 break;
1939 default:
1940 user_error
1941 << "Externally defined Func " << f.name()
1942 << " cannot have loop type " << i.for_type << " (" << i.var << ")\n";
1943 }
1944 }
1945 }
1946
1947 // Emit a warning if only some of the steps have been scheduled.
1948 bool any_scheduled = f.has_pure_definition() && f.definition().schedule().touched();
1949 for (const Definition &r : f.updates()) {
1950 any_scheduled = any_scheduled || r.schedule().touched();
1951 }
1952 if (any_scheduled) {
1953 for (size_t i = 0; i < f.updates().size(); i++) {
1954 const Definition &r = f.update((int)i);
1955 if (!r.schedule().touched()) {
1956 user_warning
1957 << "Warning: Update step " << i
1958 << " of function " << f.name()
1959 << " has not been scheduled, even though some other"
1960 << " steps have been. You may have forgotten to"
1961 << " schedule it. If this was intentional, call "
1962 << f.name() << ".update(" << i << ") to suppress"
1963 << " this warning.\n";
1964 }
1965 }
1966 }
1967
1968 // If the func is scheduled on the gpu, check that the relevant
1969 // api is enabled in the target.
1970 vector<Definition> definitions;
1971 if (f.has_pure_definition()) {
1972 definitions.push_back(f.definition());
1973 }
1974 for (const Definition &def : f.updates()) {
1975 definitions.push_back(def);
1976 }
1977
1978 for (size_t i = 0; i < definitions.size(); i++) {
1979 for (const Specialization &s : definitions[i].specializations()) {
1980 definitions.push_back(s.definition);
1981 }
1982 }
1983
1984 int racy_shift_inwards_count = 0;
1985 int allow_race_conditions_count = 0;
1986 for (const Definition &def : definitions) {
1987 const StageSchedule &s = def.schedule();
1988 set<string> parallel_vars;
1989 for (const Dim &d : s.dims()) {
1990 // We don't care about GPU parallelism here
1991 if (d.for_type == ForType::Parallel) {
1992 parallel_vars.insert(d.var);
1993 }
1994 if (!target.supports_device_api(d.device_api)) {
1995 user_error << "Schedule for Func " << f.name()
1996 << " requires " << d.device_api
1997 << " but no compatible target feature is enabled in target "
1998 << target.to_string() << "\n";
1999 }
2000 }
2001 if (s.allow_race_conditions()) {
2002 allow_race_conditions_count++;
2003 }
2004
2005 // For purposes of race-detection-warning, any split that
2006 // is the child of a parallel var is also 'parallel'.
2007 //
2008 // However, there are four types of Split, and the concept of a child var varies across them:
2009 // - For a vanilla split, inner and outer are the children and old_var is the parent.
2010 // - For rename and purify, the outer is the child and the inner is meaningless.
2011 // - For fuse, old_var is the child and inner/outer are the parents.
2012 //
2013 // (@abadams comments: "I acknowledge that this is gross and should be refactored.")
2014
2015 // (Note that the splits are ordered, so a single reverse-pass catches all these cases.)
2016 for (auto split = s.splits().rbegin(); split != s.splits().rend(); split++) {
2017 if (split->is_split() && (parallel_vars.count(split->outer) || parallel_vars.count(split->inner))) {
2018 parallel_vars.insert(split->old_var);
2019 } else if (split->is_fuse() && parallel_vars.count(split->old_var)) {
2020 parallel_vars.insert(split->inner);
2021 parallel_vars.insert(split->outer);
2022 } else if ((split->is_rename() || split->is_purify()) && parallel_vars.count(split->outer)) {
2023 parallel_vars.insert(split->old_var);
2024 }
2025 }
2026
2027 for (const auto &split : s.splits()) {
2028 // ShiftInwards used inside a parallel split can produce racy (though benignly so) code
2029 // that TSAN will complain about; issue a warning so that the user doesn't assume
2030 // the warning is legitimate.
2031 if (split.tail == TailStrategy::ShiftInwards && parallel_vars.count(split.outer)) {
2032 racy_shift_inwards_count++;
2033 }
2034 }
2035 }
2036
2037 if (target.has_feature(Target::TSAN)) {
2038 if (allow_race_conditions_count > 0) {
2039 user_warning
2040 << "Schedule for Func '" << f.name()
2041 << "'' has one or more uses of allow_race_conditions() in its schedule;\n"
2042 << "this may report benign data races when run with ThreadSanitizer.\n\n";
2043 }
2044 if (racy_shift_inwards_count > 0) {
2045 user_warning
2046 << "Schedule for Func '" << f.name()
2047 << "'' has " << racy_shift_inwards_count << " split(s) using TailStrategy::ShiftInwards inside a parallel loop;\n"
2048 << "this may report benign data races when run with ThreadSanitizer.\n"
2049 << "(Note that ShiftInwards splits may be implicitly created by\n"
2050 << "other scheduling operations, e.g. parallel() and vectorize()).\n\n";
2051 }
2052 }
2053
2054 LoopLevel store_at = f.schedule().store_level();
2055 LoopLevel compute_at = f.schedule().compute_level();
2056
2057 // Outputs must be compute_root and store_root. They're really
2058 // store_in_user_code, but store_root is close enough.
2059 if (is_output) {
2060 if (store_at.is_root() && compute_at.is_root()) {
2061 return true;
2062 } else {
2063 user_error << "Func " << f.name() << " is an output, so must"
2064 << " be scheduled compute_root (which is the default).\n";
2065 }
2066 }
2067
2068 // Otherwise inspect the uses to see what's ok.
2069 ComputeLegalSchedules legal(f, env);
2070 s.accept(&legal);
2071
2072 if (!is_output && !legal.found) {
2073 // It's not an output, and it's not called anywhere. Skip it.
2074 return false;
2075 }
2076
2077 // Check if the schedule of the inlined function is legal. Since only
2078 // pure function can be inlined, we only need to call the validator on
2079 // pure function. An inlined Halide Func with multiple stages technically
2080 // will get lowered into compute_at innermost and thus can be treated
2081 // similarly as a non-inlined Func.
2082 if (store_at.is_inlined() && compute_at.is_inlined()) {
2083 if (f.is_pure()) {
2084 validate_schedule_inlined_function(f);
2085 }
2086 return true;
2087 }
2088
2089 bool store_at_ok = false, compute_at_ok = false;
2090 const vector<ComputeLegalSchedules::Site> &sites = legal.sites_allowed;
2091 size_t store_idx = 0, compute_idx = 0;
2092 for (size_t i = 0; i < sites.size(); i++) {
2093 if (sites[i].loop_level.match(store_at)) {
2094 store_at_ok = true;
2095 store_idx = i;
2096 }
2097 if (sites[i].loop_level.match(compute_at)) {
2098 compute_at_ok = store_at_ok;
2099 compute_idx = i;
2100 }
2101 }
2102
2103 // Check there isn't a parallel loop between the compute_at and the store_at
2104 std::ostringstream err;
2105
2106 if (store_at_ok && compute_at_ok) {
2107 for (size_t i = store_idx + 1; i <= compute_idx; i++) {
2108 if (sites[i].is_parallel) {
2109 err << "Func \"" << f.name()
2110 << "\" is stored outside the parallel loop over "
2111 << sites[i].loop_level.to_string()
2112 << " but computed within it. This is a potential race condition.\n";
2113 store_at_ok = compute_at_ok = false;
2114 }
2115 }
2116 }
2117
2118 if (!store_at_ok || !compute_at_ok) {
2119 err << "Func \"" << f.name() << "\" is computed at the following invalid location:\n"
2120 << " " << schedule_to_source(f, store_at, compute_at) << "\n"
2121 << "Legal locations for this function are:\n";
2122 for (const auto &site : sites) {
2123 err << " " << schedule_to_source(f, site.loop_level, site.loop_level) << "\n";
2124 }
2125 err << "\"" << f.name() << "\" is used in the following places:\n";
2126 PrintUsesOfFunc printer(f.name(), err);
2127 s.accept(&printer);
2128
2129 user_error << err.str();
2130 }
2131
2132 return true;
2133}
2134
2135void validate_fused_group_schedule_helper(const string &fn,
2136 size_t stage_index,
2137 const Definition &def_1,
2138 const map<string, Function> &env) {
2139 internal_assert(def_1.defined());
2140 for (const auto &p : def_1.schedule().fused_pairs()) {
2141 internal_assert((fn == p.func_1) && (stage_index == p.stage_1));
2142
2143 const auto &iter1 = env.find(p.func_1);
2144 const auto &iter2 = env.find(p.func_2);
2145 internal_assert((iter1 != env.end()) && (iter2 != env.end()));
2146
2147 const Function &func_1 = iter1->second;
2148 const Function &func_2 = iter2->second;
2149 const Definition &def_2 = (p.stage_2 == 0) ? func_2.definition() : func_2.update((int)(p.stage_2 - 1));
2150 internal_assert(def_2.defined());
2151
2152 // f2.compute_with(f1, var) is allowed only if f2 has no specializations.
2153 user_assert(func_2.definition().specializations().empty())
2154 << "Func " << func_2.name() << " is scheduled to be computed with "
2155 << func_1.name() << ", so it must not have any specializations.\n";
2156
2157 // Verify that the functions being computed with are not scheduled inline.
2158 user_assert(!func_1.schedule().compute_level().is_inlined())
2159 << "Invalid compute_with: " << p.func_1 << ".s" << p.stage_1
2160 << " is scheduled inline.\n";
2161 user_assert(!func_2.schedule().compute_level().is_inlined())
2162 << "Invalid compute_with: " << p.func_2 << ".s" << p.stage_2
2163 << " is scheduled inline.\n";
2164
2165 // Verify that the functions being computed with does not have extern definitions.
2166 user_assert(!func_1.has_extern_definition())
2167 << "Invalid compute_with: " << p.func_1 << ".s" << p.stage_1
2168 << " has extern definition.\n";
2169 user_assert(!func_2.has_extern_definition())
2170 << "Invalid compute_with: " << p.func_2 << ".s" << p.stage_2
2171 << " has extern definition.\n";
2172
2173 // Verify that they are computed at the same loop level.
2174 user_assert(func_1.schedule().compute_level() == func_2.schedule().compute_level())
2175 << "Invalid compute_with: the compute levels of " << p.func_1 << ".s" << p.stage_1
2176 << " (computed at " << func_1.schedule().compute_level().to_string()
2177 << ") and " << p.func_2 << ".s" << p.stage_2 << " ("
2178 << func_2.schedule().compute_level().to_string() << ") do not match.\n";
2179
2180 const vector<Dim> &dims_1 = def_1.schedule().dims();
2181 const vector<Dim> &dims_2 = def_2.schedule().dims();
2182
2183 // Assert that the variable specified in compute_with is in the dim list.
2184 const auto &iter_1 =
2185 std::find_if(dims_1.begin(), dims_1.end(),
2186 [&p](const Dim &d) {
2187 return var_name_match(d.var, p.var_name);
2188 });
2189 user_assert(iter_1 != dims_1.end())
2190 << "Invalid compute_with: cannot find " << p.var_name << " in "
2191 << p.func_1 << ".s" << p.stage_1 << "\n";
2192
2193 const auto &iter_2 =
2194 std::find_if(dims_2.begin(), dims_2.end(),
2195 [&p](const Dim &d) {
2196 return var_name_match(d.var, p.var_name);
2197 });
2198 user_assert(iter_2 != dims_2.end())
2199 << "Invalid compute_with: cannot find " << p.var_name << " in "
2200 << p.func_2 << ".s" << p.stage_2 << "\n";
2201
2202 // Verify that their dimensions up to "var_name" are the same.
2203 size_t start_fuse_1 = (size_t)(iter_1 - dims_1.begin());
2204 size_t start_fuse_2 = (size_t)(iter_2 - dims_2.begin());
2205
2206 int n_fused = (int)(dims_1.size() - start_fuse_1 - 1); // Ignore __outermost
2207 user_assert(n_fused == (int)(dims_2.size() - start_fuse_2 - 1))
2208 << "Invalid compute_with: # of fused dims of " << p.func_1 << ".s"
2209 << p.stage_1 << " and " << p.func_2 << ".s" << p.stage_2 << " do not match.\n";
2210
2211 for (int i = 0; i < n_fused; ++i) {
2212 const Dim &d1 = dims_1[start_fuse_1 + i];
2213 const Dim &d2 = dims_2[start_fuse_2 + i];
2214 user_assert(var_name_match(d1.var, d2.var)) << "Invalid compute_with: names of dim "
2215 << i << " of " << p.func_1 << ".s"
2216 << p.stage_1 << "(" << d1.var << ") and " << p.func_2
2217 << ".s" << p.stage_2 << "(" << d2.var << ") do not match.\n";
2218 user_assert(d1.for_type == d2.for_type) << "Invalid compute_with: for types of dim "
2219 << i << " of " << p.func_1 << ".s" << p.stage_1 << "("
2220 << d1.var << " is " << d1.for_type << ") and " << p.func_2
2221 << ".s" << p.stage_2 << "(" << d2.var << " is " << d2.for_type
2222 << ") do not match.\n";
2223 user_assert(d1.device_api == d2.device_api) << "Invalid compute_with: device APIs of dim "
2224 << i << " of " << p.func_1 << ".s" << p.stage_1 << "("
2225 << d1.var << " is " << d1.device_api << ") and " << p.func_2
2226 << ".s" << p.stage_2 << "(" << d2.var << " is " << d2.device_api
2227 << ") do not match.\n";
2228 user_assert(d1.dim_type == d2.dim_type) << "Invalid compute_with: types of dim "
2229 << i << " of " << p.func_1 << ".s" << p.stage_1 << "("
2230 << d1.var << " is " << d1.dim_type << ") and " << p.func_2
2231 << ".s" << p.stage_2 << "(" << d2.var << " is " << d2.dim_type
2232 << ") do not match.\n";
2233 }
2234 }
2235}

2237void validate_fused_groups_schedule(const vector<vector<string>> &fused_groups, const map<string, Function> &env) {
2238 for (const vector<string> &group : fused_groups) {
2239 for (const auto &fn : group) {
2240 const auto &iter = env.find(fn);
2241 internal_assert(iter != env.end());
2242 if (iter->second.has_extern_definition()) {
2243 continue;
2244 }
2245
2246 validate_fused_group_schedule_helper(
2247 iter->first, 0, iter->second.definition(), env);
2248 for (size_t i = 0; i < iter->second.updates().size(); ++i) {
2249 validate_fused_group_schedule_helper(
2250 iter->first, i + 1, iter->second.updates()[i], env);
2251 }
2252 }
2253 }
2254}

2256class RemoveLoopsOverOutermost : public IRMutator {
2257 using IRMutator::visit;
2258
2259 Stmt visit(const For *op) override {
2260 if (ends_with(op->name, ".__outermost") &&
2261 is_const_one(simplify(op->extent)) &&
2262 op->device_api == DeviceAPI::None) {
2263 return mutate(substitute(op->name, op->min, op->body));
2264 } else {
2265 return IRMutator::visit(op);
2266 }
2267 }
2268
2269 Stmt visit(const LetStmt *op) override {
2270 if (ends_with(op->name, ".__outermost.loop_extent") ||
2271 ends_with(op->name, ".__outermost.loop_min") ||
2272 ends_with(op->name, ".__outermost.loop_max")) {
2273 return mutate(substitute(op->name, simplify(op->value), op->body));
2274 } else {
2275 return IRMutator::visit(op);
2276 }
2277 }
2278};

2280bool group_should_be_inlined(const vector<Function> &funcs) {
2281 return (funcs.size() == 1 &&
2282 (funcs[0].has_extern_definition() || funcs[0].definition().schedule().fused_pairs().empty()) &&
2283 funcs[0].can_be_inlined() &&
2284 funcs[0].schedule().compute_level().is_inlined());
2285}

2300
2301Stmt schedule_functions(const vector<Function> &outputs,
2302 const vector<vector<string>> &fused_groups,
2303 const map<string, Function> &env,
2304 const Target &target,
2305 bool &any_memoized) {
2306 string root_var = LoopLevel::root().lock().to_string();
2307 Stmt s = For::make(root_var, 0, 1, ForType::Serial, DeviceAPI::Host, Evaluate::make(0));
2308
2309 any_memoized = false;
2310
2311 validate_fused_groups_schedule(fused_groups, env);
2312
2313 for (size_t i = fused_groups.size(); i > 0; --i) {
2314 const vector<string> &group = fused_groups[i - 1];
2315 vector<Function> funcs;
2316 vector<bool> is_output_list;
2317
2318 for (const string &name : group) {
2319 Function f = env.find(name)->second;
2320
2321 bool is_output = false;
2322 for (const Function &o : outputs) {
2323 is_output = is_output | o.same_as(f);
2324 }
2325
2326 // The way in which the function was referred to in the
2327 // function DAG might not actually result in a use in the
2328 // code. This can happen if you inline a Tuple function,
2329 // ignoring one of the Tuple elements, and that Tuple
2330 // element is the sole call to a function with an update
2331 // definition.
2332 if (validate_schedule(f, s, target, is_output, env)) {
2333 any_memoized = any_memoized || f.schedule().memoized();
2334 funcs.push_back(f);
2335 is_output_list.push_back(is_output);
2336 }
2337 }
2338
2339 if (funcs.empty()) {
2340 continue;
2341 }
2342
2343 if (group_should_be_inlined(funcs)) {
2344 debug(1) << "Inlining " << funcs[0].name() << "\n";
2345 s = inline_function(s, funcs[0]);
2346 } else {
2347 debug(1) << "Injecting realization of " << funcs << "\n";
2348 InjectFunctionRealization injector(funcs, is_output_list, target, env);
2349 s = injector.mutate(s);
2350 internal_assert(injector.found_store_level() && injector.found_compute_level());
2351 }
2352
2353 debug(2) << s << "\n";
2354 }
2355
2356 // We can remove the loop over root now
2357 const For *root_loop = s.as<For>();
2358 internal_assert(root_loop);
2359 s = root_loop->body;
2360
2361 // We can also remove all the loops over __outermost now.
2362 s = RemoveLoopsOverOutermost().mutate(s);
2363
2364 return s;
2365}
